Your family will think you spent hours over the stove, simmering this deeply savory
ragu. We've added a dash of soy sauce for a unique umami touch. It wouldn't be complete
without a sprinkle of parmesan cheese on top!

== Prep ==

Wash and dry all produce. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil.

Quarter the @zucchini{1}(quartered lengthwise), then slice into ½-inch pieces.

Halve, peel, and finely chop the @yellow onion{1}(finely chopped).

Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(minced).

Strip the @thyme{¼%ounce}(chopped leaves) off the sprig and roughly chop the leaves.

== Cook the Beef ==

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat.

Add the @ground beef{10%ounce} and cook, breaking up the meat into pieces,
until browned but not yet cooked through. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the onions and zucchini and cook, tossing for ~{5-6%minutes}, until softened.

Add the @soy sauce{1%jar}, garlic, and thyme leaves and cook for ~{30%seconds},
until fragrant.

== Cook the Spaghetti ==

Add the @spaghetti{6%ounce} to the boiling water and cook for ~{9-11%minutes},
until al dente. Reserve 1/2 cup pasta water then drain.

== Make the Ragu ==

While the spaghetti cooks, add the @crushed tomatoes{1%box}, @?chili flakes{1%teaspoon}
and ½ cup pasta water to the pan. Simmer for about ~{10%minutes}, until thickened.

Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Toss the drained spaghetti into the sauce to combine.

Serve the tomato-garlic ragu topped with @parmesan cheese{¼%cup} and enjoy!

> Chili flakes are optional - they add a spicy kick!